 in England before the Conquest, and was reinforced by its use among the Norman invaders themselves. The Normans were the inhabitants of Normandy in northern France, whose name is a reference to the Vikings who took control of the region in the 9th century. In the 11th and 12th centuries they achieved remarkable conquests, including not only Britain but also Sicily, southern Italy, and Antioch. In the Scottish Highlands it is used as the Anglicized equivalent of Tormod ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":24,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":55,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Norman (Normannus) Kempe,De Kempe,Decampo,Decamp,Decampis was born in 1235, in Wye, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Rodger Norman DECAMPO, was 55 and his mother, Feona, was 50. He had at least 2 sons with Amila KEMP. He died in 1295, in Canterbury, Kent, England, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1235–1295":"1235–1295","1236–1295":"1236–1295","1255–1315":"1255–1315","1180–1265":"1180–1265","1185–1236":"1185–1236","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1236":"1236","1235":"1235","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","about 1255":"umbes 1255","1295":"1295","1185":"1185","1290":"1290","1180":"1180","Ollantigh Manor, Ollantigh, Wye, Ashford, Kent, England":"Wye, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, Surrey, England":"London England Temple, Newchapel, Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","england":"England","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Alsace/Lor